Class DefaultVisibilityController

    public class DefaultVisibilityController
extends java.lang.Object
implements VisibilityController
    Default implementation of the VisibilityController that enabled animation and auto hiding.

    • Constructor Detail

      • DefaultVisibilityController

        public DefaultVisibilityController(android.view.View view)
        Create a new instance of this controller with the view that will be controlled by it. Animation will be enabled and the assumption is that the view position is at the bottom of the parent component.

        Auto hiding will also be enabled by default.

        Parameters:
        view - The view

    • Method Detail

      • setEnableTouchEvents

        public void setEnableTouchEvents(@NonNull
                                 android.view.View rootView,
                                 boolean toggle)
        Enable touch events. Single touch events to the given root view will either show or toggle the visibility.
        Parameters:
        rootView - The root view where the touch listener will be attached
        toggle - If true, touch events will toggle the visibility, otherwise they will show the controlled view

      • setHideAnimator

        public void setHideAnimator(android.animation.ObjectAnimator hideAnimator)

        Parameters:
